com.esri.mo2.map.draw
Interface Symbol

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable
All Known Subinterfaces:
TextSymbol
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseSymbol, BaseTextSymbol
public interface Symbol
extends Cloneable

A Symbol can be used to draw a geometry. Normally, all that is needed to draw the geometry is the geometry itself and a Graphics2D rendering object. The Graphics2D is expected to have an appropriate Transform that converts map coordinates to the rendering surface coordinates - usually pixels. The geometry will be supplied in map coordinates.

Optionally, a Symbol may require certain Field values. The Symbol will provide a count of Fields required, and the name of those Fields. It is up to the calling code to obtain the necessary values for the corresponding Fields, and to supply them when calling the draw method.

Method Detail

draw

public void draw(FeatureGeometry g,
                 Graphics2D g2,
                 Object values)
a symbol draws a geometry object onto a pre-Transformed Graphics2D. You can obtain the world coordinate -> pixel AffineTransform using g2.getTransform().

The optional field values can be set to null if and only if getFieldCount() yields 0, otherwise values must be supplied as required. The Object parameter is very generic. If getFieldCount() yields a value of one, then the value supplied is expected to be a single Object value, for instance an Integer or String. But if getFieldCount() yields greater than 1, values must be an array of Objects, each value corresponding to the Field yielded by getFieldName(i). The type of the value(s) that can be handled by the Symbol is Symbol-specific.

Parameters:
g - the Geometry
g2 - the graphics context for rendering
values - the values of attribute fields, null == is ok and means no field values
